The paper proposes a new method for discriminant analysis, which is a common technique in machine learning and pattern recognition. The focus is on improving the performance of the method in terms of training time and accuracy. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and statistical learning (cs.SD). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the topic of discriminant analysis and its applications in machine learning and computer vision.
